  <section class="main-section" id="Polynomials">
    <header>Polynomials</header>
    <p>Given ax^b to take a derivative (differentiate) multiple the coefficient a bythe exponent b, then reduce the exponent by 1</p>
    <p>Derivative means finding the rate of change of a function</p>
    <li>(d/dx)ax^b= bax^(b-1)</li>
    <code></code>
  </section>

<br><br>

  <section class="main-section" id="Rules">
     <header>Rules</header>
    <p>The chain rule is for a function in a function, the product rule is for multiplied functions </p>
    <p>The quotient rule is divided functions</p>
    <li>dy/dx=dy/du×du/dx</li>
    <li>(fg)’ = f g’ + f’ g</li>
    <li>f'(x) = [u(x)/v(x)]' = [v(x) × u'(x) - u(x) × v'(x)]/[v(x)]2</li>
    <code></code>
  </section>


<br><br>


<section class="main-section" id="Trigonometry">
     <header>Trigonometry</header>
    <p>The derivates of cosine,tan and sine are:</p>
      <li>sin(x)'=cos(x)</li>
      <li>cos(x)'=−sin(x)</li>
      <li>tan(x)'=sec^2(x)</li>
    <p>The derivatives of cosecant, cosecant and cotangent are:</p>
  
    <li>sec(x)'=sec(x)tan(x)</li>
    <li>cot(x)'=−cosec ^2(x)</li>
    <li>cosec(x)=−cosec(x)cot(x)</li>
    <code></code>
  </section>



<br><br>




<section class="main-section" id="Exponentials">
     <header>Exponentials</header>
    <p>The basic derivation is:</p>
    <li>e^(ax)'=ae^(ax)</li> 
    <p>Two cases correspond:</p>
    <li>ex'=ex'</li>
    <li>e^-x'=e^-x</li>
    <code></code>
  </section>




  <br><br>





  <section class="main-section" id="Logarithms">
     <header>Logarithms</header>
    <p>The derivative of a natural logarithm function is: </p>
    <li>(ln x)'= 1/x</li>
    <p>Why the coefficient vanished:</p>
    <li>(ln(ax))'=1/x</li>
    <code></code>
  </section>







